<hi rend="bold">Christmas Day, Tuesday, December 25</hi><hi rend="bold superscript underline">th</hi><hi rend="bold">, 1906.</hi>
         </p>
         <p><hi rend="italic">I celebrated at 8 a.m., and preached at 11 a.m. My <ref xml:id="528">sermon</ref> was moody, melancholy, and minatory &#8211; a letting out of the waters of disappointment &amp; disgust, which have been gathering through the course of this long &amp; disastrous education conflict. <persName xml:id="1330">George Macmillan</persName> was in church. The communicants were the fewest on record:&#8211;</hi>
