         <p>In the afternoon I attended Evensong in the Abbey: on the way I met <persName xml:id="284">Sir John Wolfe Barry</persName>, who expressed very strongly his regret at the loss of the Education Bill.</p>
         <p><persName xml:id="22">Ker</persName> sent me his <term xml:id="46">'Romanes Lecture'</term> on <ref xml:id="273">'<persName xml:id="1331">Sturla</persName> the Historian'</ref>, whose very name has hitherto been unknown to me.</p>
